P.Span: Select a Deployment from the drop-down menu to filter the information. By default, your report displays information for all deployments. Thedrop-down menu also indicates the number of flows in each deployment.

The Deployed Flowstable lists the deployed flows found in the deployments. Determine which characteristics of the deployed flows aremost important to you. If more than one scheduling server containsdeployed flows, filter by theassociated scheduling server to view only the deployed flows executed by that scheduling server.
Trigger events are associated to the deployed flow, not a particular deployed job. When a trigger event filter is applied, the Deployed Jobstable is empty.

NOTE: Profiling deployed flowssearches the SAS Metadata Server for platform objects. In the case of Platform LSF scheduling, the Platform Suite for SAS must have been installed and usedfor metadata objects to have been created. If a user did not install this software, then profiling will not find Platform objects. Platform Suite for SAS was most recently available with SAS Grid Manager for Platform.

Theflows represented on this page have been gathered usingflow definition files exported from IBM Spectrum LSF Process Manager,10.1.0 or later, from SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS. Thedefinitionfiles must have been created by an administrator and made
available
to Content Assessmentprior to executing the profile.
A "(Missing)" event conditionusually indicates the flow, or job, must be manually triggered. An "lsf" event conditionindicates thetrigger is based on the job statusreturned by the LSF master host.

Span.Span: The Deployed Flowsvalue shows the number of deployed flows found in all deployments.
The Scheduling Serversvalue shows the number of unique scheduling servers in all deployments.
The Total Jobsvalue shows the number of SAS Data Integration Studio jobs associated with the deployed flows in all deployments.
The Scheduled Flowsvalue shows the number of deployed flows that have been submitted to the scheduling server.
The Flows with Dependenciesvalueshows the number of deployed flows that have dependencies on other jobs.
The Flows with Triggering Eventsvalue shows the number of deployed flows that have events to trigger the flow execution.

The SAS 9 Profile for SAS Data Integration Scheduling report enables you to explore the scheduling details of SAS Data Integration Studio deployed flows, including SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS flows.Information such as the scheduling server, triggering conditions, and dependenciesare available, as well as the SAS Data Integration Studio jobs that are part of the flow. P.Span: Content Grouping.

Some companies organize their data in their SAS systems according to data governance rules.These rules might prescribe a pattern inthe file system directoryor metadata folderstructure. At some level of the directory or folder structure, it is reasonable to assume that the data is being collected intoa logical grouping. These groupings are helpful when planning for a migration because they organize the data into smaller andmore focusedcollections.

In this report, the grouping Full Program Namedisplays the directory or folder structure of each SAS program file. By default, this grouping is the fourth level of the directory or folder structure. You can edit the level using
to change the grouping that is displayed. The specified setting groups report content and displays the grouped results by that level ofthe directory or folder structure.
For example, the default content groupingin/opt/SAS/projects/HR/payroll/ would be "HR".
Ajobis a collection of SAS tasks that create output.
Deployed Flow.
A deployed flow is agroup of jobs and their dependencies, including dependencies on other jobs, on files, or on specified dates and times.
Scheduling Server.
A scheduling
server is a server that runs deployed jobs in a scheduled deployed flow. The scheduling server determines whether conditions and dependencies have been met before a job is run.
Deployed Job.
A deployed job is a
job that has been saved in a deployment directory and can be scheduled.
SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS Flow

.A SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS flow is a SAS deployed flow converted to an IBM Spectrum LSF Process Manager flow definition. These flows are created in SAS 9 and scheduled using a Platform Process Manager server.
